# 📚 Project Babybib: System Context & Feature Glossary

**Babybib** is a professional, automated bibliography generation system specifically optimized for the **Thai academic context**, adhering strictly to the **APA 7th Edition** standard.

---

## 🎯 Core Purpose
To simplify and standardize the citation process for Thai researchers, students, and faculty by providing an automated "Citation Machine" that handles the nuances of Thai-English bilingual references.

---

## 🛠 Features (Complete List)

### 1. Citation Generation Engine
- **APA 7th Standard**: Support for all major resource types:
  - Books (Printed/Electronic)
  - Journal Articles (DOI supported)
  - Websites / Webpages
  - Reports & Grey Literature
  - Theses & Dissertations
  - Conference Proceedings
  - Audiovisual Media (YouTube, etc.)
- **Bilingual Logic**: Handles Thai and English author naming conventions differently (e.g., First Name vs. Surname ordering) as per Thai academic standards.

### 2. Smart Search v2 (Metadata Meta-Search)
Automated data filling by searching through major academic and catalog APIs:
- **ISBN/Title**: Open Library & Google Books.
- **DOI**: CrossRef & OpenAlex.
- **URLs**: Live scraping of webpage meta tags.
- **Intelligent Detection**: Automatically identifies if a source is likely a Book or a Journal based on the identifier provided.

### 3. Bibliography Management
- **Project/Folder System**: Users can group citations into specific "Projects" for different papers.
- **Live Preview**: Real-time rendering of the citation in the browser.
- **Copy-to-Clipboard**: Instant copying of formatted citations with "Hanging Indent" CSS styling preserved.

### 4. User System
- **Secure Authentication**: Register, Login, Logout.
- **Email Verification**: Ensuring valid academic users.
- **Profile Management**: Saved project history and settings.

### 5. Administrative Features
- **Announcement System**: Push notifications (Toasts/Popups) for system updates.
- **User Dashboard**: Manage users, roles, and activity.
- **Audit Logs**: Track generation errors or smart search failures for debugging.
- **Backup System**: Automated database snapshots.

---

## 🎨 Design System & Aesthetics (Color Palette)

The system follows a **"Friendly Academic SaaS"** aesthetic: clean, premium, and highly legible.

| Token | Value | Hex/Preview |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Primary** | Violet / Purple | `#8B5CF6` |
| **Primary Dark** | Deep Violet | `#7C3AED` |
| **Primary Light** | Soft Lavender | `#EDE9FE` |
| **Brand Gradient** | Indigo to Pink | `linear-gradient(135deg, #6366F1, #8B5CF6, #D946EF)` |
| **Success** | Emerald Green | `#10B981` |
| **Danger** | Red | `#EF4444` |
| **Background** | Off-White / Gray | `#F9FAFB` |

### Typography
- **Thai Font**: `Tahoma` (Primary for maximum compatibility and clarity in academic text).
- **English Font**: `Comfortaa`, `-apple-system`, `SF Pro Display`.

### UI Style
- **Corners**: Large border-radius (`1rem` / `16px`) for a friendly, modern feel.
- **Elevations**: Subtle multi-layered shadows for depth.
- **Dark Mode**: Fully supported, switching to deep charcoal/black backgrounds with high-contrast text.

---

## 🚀 Future Roadmap (Laravel Migration)
- **Livewire Integration**: Zero-refresh citation editing.
- **Advanced Export**: Direct `.docx` (Word) and `.pdf` generation.
- **Collaboration**: Sharing project folders between researchers.
- **AI Citation Helper**: Using LLMs to clean up "dirty" metadata from old sources.

---

## 🧩 Agent Guidance
When working on this project:
1. **Prioritize APA 7th Accuracy**: Changes to formatting logic MUST match the official APA 7 manual.
2. **Handle Thai Names Carefully**: Thai citations often use the full name without reversing (unlike English).
3. **Maintain the Premium Aesthetic**: Avoid generic Bootstrap/Tailwind looks; stick to the custom violet-gradient design language.
